Aedes.
Male and female Aedes 16 wing landmarks raw coordinates allowing the morphometric comparisons of Ae. albopictus with Ae. scutellaris, Ae. aegypti with Ae. scutellaris, and Ae. albopictus with Ae. aegypti.

The name of each file contains the following abbreviations
LM landmarks (their raw coordinates)
F females
M males
aeg aegypti
alb albopictus
scu scutellaris
Each file neme ends by the sample sizes of each species. For instance "LM_Malb-scu_41-36" means Landmarks of 41 male Aedes albopictus followed by the landmarks of 36 male Aedes scutellaris. 

Anopheles. There are two subfolders "min-har" and "saw-pse".
min = An. minimus
har = An. harrisoni
saw = An. sawadwongporni
pse = An. pseudowillmori

subfolder "min-har"
16 wing landmarks of female An. minimus Theobald, 1901 and An. harrisoni Harbach & Manguin, 2007. They are based on the same number of landmarks (16) as for the Aedes species, and collected in the same order.

Each file contains the raw coordinates of two species, ordered according to the name of the file. For instance:
"Female_67 min 22 har.txt" contains the raw coordinates (16 landmarks) of 22 An. minimus followed by the raw coordinate (16 landmarks) of 22 harrisoni

subfolder "saw-pse"
The raw coordinates correspond to 17 landmarks. Here, different operators, T and JP, used a different sampling of the mosquitoes: 41,36 and 26,28, respectively.
"Female_sawad_pseudo_42-36.txt"

Glossinidae. Two subspecies of Glossina palpalis from Ivory Coast (Côte d’Ivoire): G. palpalis gambiensis (Gpg) and G. palpalis palpalis (Gpp) [9]. Eleven landmarks were annotated by two operators: B(erte) and TA(Ta).

Muscidae. 10 landmarks for male Stomoxys pullus Austen, 1909 and Stomoxys uruma Shinonaga et Kano, 1966.

Reduviidae. The North American Triatoma protracta (Uhler) (1894).: T. p. woodi and T. p. protracta. 13 landmarks.

Tabanidae.  Tabanus megalops Walker, 1854 and Tabanus striatus Fabricius, 1787: 22 landmarks

Psychodidae. Sergentomyia hodgsoni (Sinton, 1933) and Phlebotomus stantoni (Newstead 1914). 12 landmarks.

